article.description: Marvell Harris had 15 of his 25 points in the second half and Fresno State rallied to beat Wyoming 71-60 on Tuesday night.
article.headline: Harris scores 25, Fresno State beats Wyoming 71-60
article.linkText: Harris scores 25, Fresno State beats Wyoming 71-60
article.story: FRESNO, Calif. -- Marvell Harris had 15 of his 25 points in the second half and Fresno State rallied to beat Wyoming 71-60 on Tuesday night. Paul Watson had 12 points, Karachi Edo and Cezar Guerrero added 11 apiece and Cullen Russo chipped in 10 points and grabbed 10 rebounds for Fresno State (14-7, 5-3 Mountain West). Trailing 37-33 at the break, Fresno State opened the second half with an 11-3 run and led 44-40 at the midway mark. The Bulldogs held Wyoming without a basket for 7:38. Russo nailed a 3-pointer with 3:26 left to give Fresno State a 61-51 lead. The Bulldogs made eight free throws down the stretch and Guerrero hit a jump shot to secure the win. Fresno State won the rebound battle 39-26 and scored 22 points in the paint. Josh Adams led Wyoming (10-12, 3-6) with 32 points, including 5 of 11 3-pointers.
